        <h1>Provident Electric</h1>

        <p>The Provident Electric facility represents specialized commercial construction designed to support the unique operational needs of an electrical contracting business. Located in Seattle, this project required understanding the specific requirements of a contractor facility—from equipment storage and workspace organization to office areas and vehicle access.</p>

        <p>We worked closely with Provident Electric to design and build a facility that maximizes operational efficiency while providing a professional environment for their team and clients. The project integrated warehouse-style workspace for equipment and materials, office areas for administration and project planning, and carefully planned vehicle access for fleet management.</p>

        <p>Building for fellow contractors demands an extra level of accountability—they understand construction quality and recognize craftsmanship when they see it. This project showcases our ability to deliver commercial facilities that meet the demanding standards of industry professionals.</p>

        <h3>Project Highlights</h3>
        <ul style="line-height: 2; margin-bottom: 2rem;">
          <li>Purpose-built contractor facility combining warehouse and office space</li>
          <li>Efficient layout supporting electrical contracting operations</li>
          <li>Robust infrastructure and heavy-duty electrical capacity</li>
          <li>Professional office areas and client-facing spaces</li>
          <li>Strategic vehicle access and equipment storage solutions</li>
          <li>Construction quality meeting contractor-level standards</li>
        </ul>

        <p>The Provident Electric project demonstrates our versatility in commercial construction and our ability to deliver specialized facilities that truly serve the operational needs of our clients. When contractors choose Northway to build their own facilities, it speaks to the trust and reputation we've earned in the industry.</p>
